<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">12</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">PSI 156</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Social Anthropology</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">8</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">23.08.2024</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The aim of this course is to teach anthropology, especially what socio-cultural anthropology is and how this science Analyzes Human Relations and culture. However, this discipline teaches us how to approach cultural problems and what solutions we can find. This course shows that many human behaviors are closely related to culture-based perception. In this context, it teaches to analyze differences in human behavior by trying to understand what these behaviors mean in its environment, rather than judging them by attributing good, bad, Strange, etc.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=325693&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
