<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">12</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ACU 153</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">How to Read a Photo?</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Have the necessary equipment to read the photos they see. In this way, they will understand the photos that exist in both the media and our daily (private) lives, change the way they interpret them, understand how visual language is used in visual culture, and gain the ability to interpret them.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=325727&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Psychology</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">12</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ACU 154</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Cultural Memory: How We Remember, Why We Forget</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Students who successfully complete the course will recognize ‘cultural memory &apos; as a concept and content. In addition, they will be able to understand and analyze how and in what forms cultural memory feeds our existence, identity in relation to concepts such as remembering, forgetting, nostalgia, popular culture, individually and culturally in our daily lives</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=325728&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
</Row>
